author: kfogel
msg: Disentangle some stuff that was starting to get tangled in the FAQ.
The questions "permissions" and "wedged-repos" overlapped a lot.  At
the same time, their labels were not accurate: "permissions" was about
much more than just permissions, and "wedged-repos" was really about
how to run recovery.  Independently of all that, "permissions" and
"reposperms" were sort of duplicates too.
This change organizes content better, and gives some new labels, while
leaving old labels around for URL compatibility.
* project_faq.html
(reposperms): Answer all permissions questions here.
(stuck-bdb-repos): New name for "permissions", old name remains.
Rewrite, including new material about running out of disk space,
from Arkadiusz Miskiewicz <arekm@pld-linux.org>.  Just refer to
newly-expanded "reposperms" question for permissions details.
(bdb-recovery): New name for "wedged-repos", old name remains.
